|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref name="DecennialCensus">{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/prod/www/decennial.html|title=Census of Population and Housing|publisher=Census.gov|accessdate=June 4, 2016}}</ref>
}}As of 2021, the [[2020 United States census|US Census]] QuickFacts reports that Elkins Park is 62.6% white alone, 27.6% Black or African American, 4.9% two or more races, 4.2% Hispanic or Latino, and 3.8% Asian alone.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=U.S. Census Bureau QuickFacts: Elkins Park CDP, Pennsylvania |url=https://www.census.gov/quickfacts/fact/table/elkinsparkcdppennsylvania/LFE305221 |access-date=2023-03-29 |website=census.gov}}</ref>

The total population was 6,901 people according to 2020 Census figures.<ref name=":1" />

The [[median household income]] in 2022 dollars was $121,135, the median family income was $158,000 and the median income for married-couple families was $180,189.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile?g=160XX00US4223128 |access-date=2023-03-29 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref> The per capita income was $72,072.<ref name=":0" />

